Consecutively, (the topic of) Attributive Consciousness will now be expounded. The nature of it is described thus:-
While it is self-luminous, non-sentient sub- stance, it is &lsquo;objectivated&rsquo; (sa-vishayatvam) (ie., some object always constituting its content);
While it is pervasive (Vibhu), it is of the nature of substance (Dravya), and attribute (Guna) like light;
It is the illuminant of objects;
It is Intellect or Intelligence (Buddhi) etc. Attributive Consciousness&quot; is, to God and the Eternals (Nityas), ever eternal and pervasive (or diffusive); to the Bound (Baddha-souls) it
